# netlify-cms-widget-{{kebabCase name}}
{{ titleCase name}} widget for Netlify CMS.

## Install and Usage

### As an npm package:

```shell
npm install netlify-cms-widget-{{name}}
```

```js
import CMS from 'netlify-cms'
{{#if multiple}}
import * as {{pascalCase name}}Widget from 'netlify-cms-widget-{{name}}'
CMS.registerWidget('{{name}}', {{pascalCase name}}Widget.Control, {{pascalCase name}}Widget.Preview)
{{else}}
import {{pascalCase name}}Widget from 'netlify-cms-widget-{{name}}'
CMS.registerWidget('{{name}}', {{pascalCase name}}Widget)
{{/if}}
```
Add to your config.yml:
```yaml
    fields:
      - { name: <fieldname>, label: <fieldlabel>, widget: {{name}} }
```

### Via `script` tag:
Note: we use `netlify-cms-extended` here, see: netlify/netlify-cms#1292
```html
<script src="https://unpkg.com/netlify-cms-extended/dist/extended.js"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/netlify-cms-widget-{{name}}"></script>
<script>
  {{#if multiple}}
  CMS.registerWidget(
    '{{name}}',
    NetlifyCMSWidget{{pascalCase name}}.Control,
    NetlifyCMSWidget{{pascalCase name}}.Preview
  )
  {{else}}
  CMS.registerWidget('{{name}}', NetlifyCMSWidget{{pascalCase name}})
  {{/if}}
</script>
```
